  "text": "To investigate whether cells representing phenotypes with more osteoblast-like characteristics than ϩ / ϩ LDA11 cells express different receptors, we examined cytokine responsiveness in two other murine cell lines, MBA13.2 and MC3T3-E1. MBA13.2 cells have several phenotypic characteristics of osteoblastic cells, including expression of type I and type IV collagen, as well as PTH receptors [CITATION_1] . MC3T3-E1 cells represent a differentiated osteoblastic phenotype, as evidenced by the fact that they are able to secrete and mineralize matrix [CITATION_2] . As shown in Fig. 4 A , MBA13.2 cells did not respond to IL-6, but they responded to IL-6 in the presence of sIL-6R. These cells also responded to IL-11, with tyrosine phosphorylation of gp130 homodimers. Unlike ϩ / ϩ LDA.11 cells, MBA13.2 cells responded to LIF, CNTF ϩ sCNTFR ␣ (but not to CNTF alone), and OSM, with the phosphorylation of gp130 and LIFR ␤, indicating that in difference to ϩ/ϩLDA11, MBA13.2 cells express LIFR␤.",
